Rules for configuring a custom component
========================================
- We cannot defined a custom component with predefined html elements names.
    <header> //invalid

-  Every component name must be either in PascalCase(First letter in every word in uppercase) or lowercase.
- For actual DOM, we use lowercase and for Virtual DOM we use PascalCase.
    PascalCase: HeaderComponent
    lowercase: headercomponent


Class Component in ReactJS
--------------------------
- It is a JS class which extends "React.component" base class.
- Syntax:
    class LoginComponent extends React.Component{}

- JS class comprises of only the following members:
    1. Properties: Data is stored
    2. Method : Functionality
    3. Accessors : setters and getters
    4. Constructor
- Component class can render VirtualDOM elements by using "render()" method.
- "render()' method returns JSX.


Q: Can we define a variable in class?
A: NO.

Q: Can we define a variable in class?
A: NO.

